## Scenario 3 — Chemical + Ergonomic During Manual Drum Handling
##
## Multi-hazard compound activation: two hazard types fire in parallel
## on the same task (manual drum lift-and-tilt). Chemical side fires
## OSHA HCS + ACGIH TLV (+ skin notation for dermal). Ergonomic side
## fires NIOSH Lifting Equation + ANSI Z365 + OSHA GDC. Both pathways
## are active — neither cancels the other.
##
## Baseline triples extracted from ehs-ontology-v3.2.ttl (line 1238).

PREFIX ehs: <http://example.org/ehs-ontology#>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>

ASK {
    ehs:Scenario_ChemErgo_DrumHandling rdf:type ehs:ContextualComplianceActivation ;
        ehs:triggeredByType       ehs:ChemicalHazard ,
                                  ehs:ErgonomicHazard ;
        ehs:hasActionContext      ehs:TransferAction ;
        ehs:hasContextCondition   ehs:ProductionFloor ;
        ehs:activatesFramework    ehs:OSHA_Framework ,
                                  ehs:GHS_Framework ,
                                  ehs:ACGIH_Framework ,
                                  ehs:NIOSH_Framework ,
                                  ehs:ANSI_Framework .
}
